Data Cleaning

It appears that this person only answered the first question before submitting. How do we want to handle this row? Suppose we decide we simply dont trust the data (not even the 1 for Pcredit). Then, we might decide to take this row out entirely.

x <- x[x$UorG != "",]

A suggestion from last class

Can we just replace all blanks with NA simultaneously?

x[x==""] <- NA
table(x$UorG)
## 
##      Graduate student               Neither Undergraduate student 
##                    22                     1                    69

We can still abbreviate the labels:

x$UorG[x$UorG == "Graduate student"] <- "Grad"
x$UorG[x$UorG == "Undergraduate student"] <- "Undergrad"
table(x$UorG)
## 
##      Grad   Neither Undergrad 
##        22         1        69

Lets take a look at Year:

table(x$Year)
## 
## 1 = freshman or first year grad  2 = sophomore or 2nd year grad 
##                              24                              31 
##     3 = junior or 3rd year grad     4 = senior or 4th year grad 
##                              16                              16 
##                 Beyond 4th year

x$Year[x$Year == "1 = freshman or first year grad"] <- "1"
unique(x$Year)
## [1] "1"                              "2 = sophomore or 2nd year grad"
## [3] "4 = senior or 4th year grad"    "3 = junior or 3rd year grad"   
## [5] NA                               "Beyond 4th year"

To save ourselves some typing:

x$Year[grep("2 =", x$Year)] <- "2"
x$Year[grep("3 =", x$Year)] <- "3"
x$Year[grep("4 =", x$Year)] <- "4"
x$Year[grep("Beyond", x$Year)] <- "4+"

# input: 'z' a vector that is supposedly numeric but has nonnumeric values
# output: a vector of indices corresponding to those nonnumeric values
findNonNumbers <- function(z) {
  return(which(is.na(as.numeric(z))))
}

temp <- findNonNumbers(x$Height)
## Warning in which(is.na(as.numeric(z))): NAs introduced by coercion
temp
## [1]  8 10 30 37 54 63 66 74
x$Height[temp[1]] # nothing to do, started as an NA
## [1] NA
x$Height[temp[2]] <- 6*12+1
x$Height[temp[2]]
## [1] "73"
x$Height[temp[3]] <- 6*12+3
x$Height[temp[6]] <- 5*12+3
x$Height[temp[7]] <- 4*12+2
x$Height <- as.numeric(x$Height)
hist(x$Height)
